    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Electromagnetic radiation emitted by high-energy particles following a curved path at close to the speed of light as in the variety of particle accelerator known as a synchrotron. It is also produced naturally by charged particles moving through magnetic fields. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
